Encodes numeric counts as steno key sets and merges or subtracts stroke segments. A count bank maps a spec string (like "AOEU") to bit weights: the i-th key carries weight 2^i, LSB-first, so `apply_count("T", "AOEU", 5)` sets keys A and U (weights 1 and 4) to yield "TAU". Keys must be vowels (middle bank) or right-bank keys; the bank's `max` is always 2^width - 1.

`count_bank(spec)` parses and validates a spec, rejecting keys outside vowel/right banks and specs wider than 32 bits. `apply_count(segment, spec, count)` merges the keys encoding `count` into a segment; errors if count exceeds the bank's max or a count key already exists in the segment. `merge_strokes(a, b)` unions two parsed strokes key-by-key, erroring on any shared key; `subtract_strokes(a, b)` removes b's keys from a, returning `None` if b is not a subset (the shape did not fuse). `add_key(segment, key)` inserts a single vowel or right-bank key, erroring if already present. All functions use `parse_stroke` and `render_stroke` from `super::keys`; stroke parsing is also the coupling point — formats must align.